Chapter 42. 4. annus. etc.: Africa and Asia, the two most important senatorial provinces, were every year distributed, as a rule by lot, among the two senior ex-consuls. As the interval which was usually allowed to elapse between the consulship and this proconsul- ship seems to have fluctuated between five and thirteen years, it is impossible to determine exactly the date here alluded to. Agricola had been appointed consul in the fall 01 77 min, and Tacitus left Rome, undoubtedly in some official capacity, about SSUQO (cp. ch. 45, 4).
